        <prompt>What was the significance of the "Union Leagues" in the South?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Organizations that helped freedmen exercise political rights</option>
            <option letter="b">Confederate veteran groups</option>
            <option letter="c">Northern business associations</option>
            <option letter="d">Agricultural cooperatives</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Union Leagues were organizations that helped freedmen exercise their new political rights, providing protection and education about voting and citizenship.</explanation>
