    <question>
        <prompt>What impact did President Johnson's veto of the Freedmen's Bureau Bill have?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Increased conflict between Congress and the President</option>
            <option letter="b">Strengthened Reconstruction efforts</option>
            <option letter="c">Improved race relations</option>
            <option letter="d">Expanded federal programs</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Johnson's veto of the Freedmen's Bureau Bill in 1866 intensified conflict between Congress and the President, leading to more radical Reconstruction measures.</explanation>
